<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q22_v10" title="Q22_v10" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>
      La diagonal <m:math><m:mi>d</m:mi></m:math> de un prisma recto de base rectangular se calcula como
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>d</m:mi>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:msqrt>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>a</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>b</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>c</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:msqrt>
      </m:math>, donde
      <m:math><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math>,
      <m:math><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:math>
      y
      <m:math><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:math>
      son las medidas de sus aristas.
    </p>
    <p>
      Considera un prisma recto de base rectangular cuya diagonal interior mide
      <m:math>
        <m:msqrt>
          <m:mn>260</m:mn>
        </m:msqrt>
      </m:math>
      cm y dos de sus aristas miden
      <m:math><m:mn>9</m:mn></m:math>
      cm y
      <m:math><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:math>
      cm, respectivamente.
      ¿Cuál de las siguientes afirmaciones describe mejor la medida de la tercera arista de este prisma?
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        La tercera arista mide entre 6 cm y 7 cm.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">
          Incorrecto. Si la diagonal mide
          <m:math>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>260</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:math>
          cm y las otras aristas miden
          <m:math><m:mn>9</m:mn></m:math>
          cm y
          <m:math><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:math>
          cm, entonces la tercera arista cumple
          <m:math>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>260</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>9</m:mn>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>260</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:mn>81</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:mn>100</m:mn>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>79</m:mn>
          </m:math>,
          por lo que
          <m:math>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>79</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
            <m:mo>≈</m:mo>
            <m:mn>8,9</m:mn>
          </m:math>
          cm. Como
          <m:math><m:mn>8,9</m:mn></m:math>
          no está entre
          <m:math><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:math>
          y
          <m:math><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:math>,
          la afirmación es falsa.
        </qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        La tercera arista mide entre 8 cm y 10 cm.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">
          ¡Correcto! Si
          <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>
          es la tercera arista, entonces
          <m:math>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>260</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>9</m:mn>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>260</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:mn>81</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:mn>100</m:mn>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>79</m:mn>
          </m:math>.
          Por tanto,
          <m:math>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>79</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
            <m:mo>≈</m:mo>
            <m:mn>8,9</m:mn>
          </m:math>
          cm, y
          <m:math><m:mn>8,9</m:mn></m:math>
          sí está entre
          <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math>
          y
          <m:math><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:math>.
        </qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        La tercera arista mide entre 12 cm y 14 cm.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">
          Incorrecto. Al usar la fórmula de la diagonal se obtiene
          <m:math>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>260</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:mn>81</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:mn>100</m:mn>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>79</m:mn>
          </m:math>,
          así que
          <m:math>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>79</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
            <m:mo>≈</m:mo>
            <m:mn>8,9</m:mn>
          </m:math>
          cm. Como
          <m:math><m:mn>8,9</m:mn></m:math>
          no está entre
          <m:math><m:mn>12</m:mn></m:math>
          y
          <m:math><m:mn>14</m:mn></m:math>,
          la afirmación es falsa.
        </qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        La tercera arista mide más de 20 cm.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">
          Incorrecto. La tercera arista vale
          <m:math>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>79</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
            <m:mo>≈</m:mo>
            <m:mn>8,9</m:mn>
          </m:math>
          cm, porque
          <m:math>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>260</m:mn>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>9</m:mn>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>79</m:mn>
          </m:math>.
          Como
          <m:math><m:mn>8,9</m:mn></m:math>
          es menor que
          <m:math><m:mn>20</m:mn></m:math>,
          no mide más de
          <m:math><m:mn>20</m:mn></m:math>
          cm.
        </qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Escribir la fórmula de la diagonal del prisma</strong></p>
            <p>Para un prisma recto de base rectangular, la diagonal interior cumple:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msqrt>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mi>c</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:msqrt>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Reemplazar los datos del problema</strong></p>
            <p>La diagonal mide:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msqrt>
                  <m:mn>260</m:mn>
                </m:msqrt>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Dos aristas miden:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>9</m:mn>
              </m:math>
              <m:math><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:math>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>10</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Sea <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> la tercera arista. Entonces:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msqrt>
                  <m:mn>260</m:mn>
                </m:msqrt>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msqrt>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mn>9</m:mn>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:msqrt>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Elevar al cuadrado ambos lados</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mn>260</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>9</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Calculamos los cuadrados conocidos:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>9</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>81</m:mn>
              </m:math>
              <m:math><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:math>
              <m:math>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>100</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mn>260</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>81</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>100</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Despejar la tercera arista</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>260</m:mn>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>81</m:mn>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>100</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>79</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Como una arista representa una longitud, tomamos la raíz positiva:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msqrt>
                  <m:mn>79</m:mn>
                </m:msqrt>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Aproximar y comparar con los intervalos</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msqrt>
                  <m:mn>79</m:mn>
                </m:msqrt>
                <m:mo>≈</m:mo>
                <m:mn>8,9</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces la tercera arista mide aproximadamente 8,9 cm.</p>
            <p>Ese valor está entre 8 cm y 10 cm.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La afirmación correcta es: <strong>La tercera arista mide entre 8 cm y 10 cm</strong>.</p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la respuesta correcta es la <strong>opción B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>